# .rules — GPU & inference monitor (OSS)

> **Single source of truth for this repo — read this first.** Humans and AI assistants (Claude,
> Gemini, Codex, …) follow it; `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, and `GEMINI.md` all point here. Keep it
> **concise and current**: the *plan* lives in [`ROADMAP.md`](./ROADMAP.md), the *why* in
> [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](./ARCHITECTURE.md), the *how-to* in [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](./CONTRIBUTING.md). Don't duplicate them here.

## What this repo is
An **open-source, Apache-2.0**, native **GPU & AI-inference monitor** written in **Rust** — a single
binary with **two first-class frontends**: a GPU-accelerated **GUI** *and* a terminal **CLI/TUI**. In
the spirit of Zed/Ghostty (native craft) and Ollama (DX): fast, single-binary, **no Electron**.
NVIDIA/NVML first; inference-aware (Ollama/vLLM/Triton) is the wedge. **Working name: TBD** (the repo
is still named `agent`; the rename is a pre-M1 task).

> **Status:** the **M0 scaffold is in place** — the workspace builds, `cargo run -p agent -- ps`
> shows the mock source, and `gui`/`top` point at their milestones (M1/M3). The crates
> (`core`/`collector`/`ui`/`cli`/`app`) are skeletons; real metrics begin at M1. The repo is still
> named `agent` pending the rename.

## Commands
| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Build | `cargo build` |
| Run the GUI (default) | `cargo run -p agent -- gui` |
| Run the live TUI | `cargo run -p agent -- top` |
| One-shot snapshot (scriptable) | `cargo run -p agent -- ps` · `… -- ps --json` |
| Run with **no GPU** (mock source) | append `--mock` (or `AGENT_SOURCE=mock`) |
| Full local gate before pushing | `cargo xtask ci` (build + clippy + fmt + test + deny) |
| Test (headless, no GPU needed) | `cargo test` |
| Lint — must be clean | `cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings` and `cargo fmt --all --check` |
| Supply chain | `cargo deny check` |

- **Stable Rust, one host target.** No nightly, no cross-compile, no `sudo`, no codegen step — that
  was the old eBPF project. NVML needs **no root**; the **mock collector** means every command works
  with no GPU and no driver present.

## Stack & layout
- **Rust** (stable). **GUI:** `egui` on `wgpu`. **TUI:** `ratatui`. **GPU values:** `nvml-wrapper`
  (NVML); **DCGM** optional (richer/MIG). **Inference:** Ollama `/api/ps`, vLLM/Triton Prometheus.
- Model after: `nvtop`/`btop` (the monitor), **Zed**/**Ghostty** (native craft), **Ollama** (DX).
```
crates/core       data model: snapshots, ring-buffer series, the collector + sink traits. The spine.
crates/collector  sources: nvml, dcgm (optional), inference scraper, mock
crates/ui         GUI frontend (lib): wgpu/egui — charts, gauges, process table, GPU grid
crates/cli        terminal frontend (lib): one-shot ps/--json + the live `top` TUI (ratatui)
crates/export     machine sinks (lib): prometheus, otlp, splunk — wired in M8 (the `Sink` trait is in core)
crates/app        the single binary: subcommand dispatch (gui/top/ps; serve in M9), wires collector → core → {ui|cli|sinks}
xtask             build/dev orchestration (dev-only, never shipped)
```

## Invariants — do not trade these away
The *rule* is here; the *why* is in [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](./ARCHITECTURE.md) (Design decisions).
- **Headless engine; every surface is a pure view.** `collector` → `core`; the GUI, TUI, one-shot CLI,
  and machine sinks **only render `core`** — no surface calls NVML/DCGM/Ollama/Prometheus directly.
  This is what keeps the app testable headless, demoable without a GPU, scriptable, exportable, and
  remote-capable.
- **Two first-class frontends, one binary.** A native GUI *and* a CLI/TUI, at parity — every metric in
  all surfaces. The CLI is real (stable `--json`, exit codes, `--watch`), not a toy.
- **Native, no Electron, single binary.** GUI via `wgpu`, TUI via `ratatui`; fast cold start; static
  where the driver allows. The craft bar is the reason to build this over a web app.
- **Integrate, don't reimplement.** Exporters (Prometheus/OTLP/Splunk, M8) are machine-facing pure
  views of `core` — we expose data, never store/dashboard/alert. Plug into the user's stack.
- **Local-first, zero-config.** Launch → local GPUs (and any running Ollama/vLLM) visible, no
  server/account/config. Exporters (M8), remote (M9), and persistence (M7) are additive.
- **A monitor must never be a hog.** Sample sanely, **render on change** (idle when backgrounded),
  bound every buffer, and surface our own CPU/GPU/RAM. The tool that watches usage cannot cause it.
- **Inference awareness is the wedge** — Ollama-first model attribution + serving KPIs are why this
  exists; raw hardware counters are commodity.
- **Vendor-neutral behind a trait.** NVIDIA/NVML first, but `core`/`ui`/`cli` never assume NVIDIA — a
  new GPU vendor is a new `collector`, nothing else. The **mock** source is permanent.

## Code conventions
- `cargo fmt` + `cargo clippy` clean. **No `unwrap`/`expect`/`panic!` outside tests** (workspace
  `deny` lints; `clippy.toml` re-allows them in tests). All crates are stable-Rust, `std`.
- **Frontend parity:** adding a metric means updating the model once and the three thin renderers —
  never duplicating logic, never a GUI-only metric. A GUI-only metric is a design smell.
- **Bounded everything:** ring buffers are fixed-capacity; caches (PID→name) are pruned; nothing grows
  with uptime. Sampling runs on a background task at a sane interval; the UI never blocks on a sample.
- **Render on change, not on a spin loop:** adaptive frame rate in the GUI; low redraw cost in the TUI
  (don't spin a remote CPU over SSH).
- **The CLI is a contract:** `ps --json` has stable field names + exit codes; `--watch` streams JSON
  lines. Treat it like an API — additive changes only.
- **Frameworks are decisions:** GUI `egui`/`wgpu`, TUI `ratatui`, GPU `nvml-wrapper` — see
  [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](./ARCHITECTURE.md); don't swap them casually.

## Repo etiquette
- Commits: one logical change each, imperative subject. **Never add AI co-author / attribution
  trailers.** Never commit secrets or fetched/generated data.
- Work in milestones (`M0`…`M10`, laddering to `v1.0.0`); close each with a tag + a working demo +
  green CI, and don't start one until the prior is green. Record any significant, hard-to-reverse
  decision in [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](./ARCHITECTURE.md) (Design decisions).

